ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course covered the fundamental concepts and techniques in biology. I would highly recommend this course to non-biology background students who want to conduct research in biological/biomedical sciences as it is very helpful as a boot camp training.
Biology overview for engineering or physical science students who have had no or little experience with biology.

A good class for introduction to / review of biological concepts. If you have a fairly strong background in these topics, then you'd probably be better off reviewing them with an old textbook or online resources. If you're background is quite limited, however, this class should be very useful.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course deepened my understanding about many biological concepts. It is a good preparation for my research in PEB discipline.
